meaning_str.bing:
n. 标题；头衔；职称；所有权凭证
v. （给书、乐曲等）加标题
网络. 题目；书名；网页标题

标题；头衔；职称；所有权凭证

标题；题目；称号；名称；称呼；敬称；头衔；职称；职务；冠军；优胜者；所有权；产权；权利；授权；资格；地位；封号；爵位；（书籍、文章、艺术作品等的）名字；片名；曲名；（比赛或竞赛的）冠名；（法律上的）权利证明；（宗教职位的）任命资格
给…加标题；定题目；为…命名；给…取名；为…加上题目；授予头衔

1.en: But there is no doubt that he deserves the title "outstanding player of his generation" .
1.cn: 但是毫无疑问，他无愧于“一代杰出球员”这一称号。

2.en: Subsequently he made this the title of his own movie, no doubt as a further gesture of anti-European defiance.
2.cn: 再后来，他竟以此作为自己的电影的名字。毫无疑问，这是他蔑视欧洲人的进一步表现。

3.en: Her mother did not get past the title before breaking down.
3.cn: 她的母亲还没读完标题就崩溃了。

0.en: She's got the astrologer in her. I think she liked the title more than anything.
0.cn: 她流着占星家的血。我觉得她最爱的就是标题。

1.en: It's a working title. I'm Kevin. Oh. Penny. Nice to meet you.
1.cn: 这只是暂定名。我叫凯文。我叫佩妮。幸会幸会。

2.en: She is great at promotion. That title gets longer every time I hear it.
2.cn: 她确实很擅长推销，那职位名越来越长了。

3.en: So you can't lose, it's there in the title. Wonderfulness is baked right in.
3.cn: 所以没问题，片名说明了一切，包你美妙得不得了。

4.en: And how old were you when you published this paper that has a title I can barely understand? 23.
4.cn: 那你发表这篇我连题目也看不懂的论文时是多大？呃，二十三岁。

5.en: "All right, I tried." That should be the title of your autobiography. Ooh, a second-degree burn.
5.cn: “好吧，我尽力了”，你应该用这句当你自传的书名。有人被损得皮焦肉烂啦。

6.en: Your sister did tell me that you would do anything in your power to prevent me from claiming my title.
6.cn: 你姐姐告诉我你会动用一切力量阻止我主张我的权利。

7.en: What am I supposed to do? Do you want me to write a piece called We're All Fucked? Yes! That's a perfect title!
7.cn: 我该怎么办呢？写篇文章，题目就叫《我们都玩完了》？好啊！简直完美！

8.en: He's also heir to his grandfather's title for reasons too complicated to bore you with. So it's very neat and tidy.
8.cn: 他还要继承他爷爷的头衔，原因复杂，我就不烦你了，所以很利落。

9.en: So Mac and C.H.E.E.S.E.. That's the title. Yeah. You know they really lucked out that the initials spell cheese. That is lucky.
9.cn: 麦克与吉事，那就是剧名，幸好缩写刚好是吉事。真是幸好。

10.en: By our Constitution and the laws of our land, including Section Blah-Blah of the Blah-Blah Act and Section Blah-Blah of Title Blah-Blah, Paragraph Bullshit-Bullshit.
10.cn: 凭借国会和我们国家的法律包括什么什么法第多少多少章，还有某某法令第多少多少章，第哪条狗屁款。

11.en: So, I don't really have a job title or even a set place to work, so I kind of just float around and make sure everyone has what they need. 4:00, Your Honor. Don't forget to take your medicine.
11.cn: 我的工作没有职称，也没有固定的工作地点，所以我就转来转去。确保所有人得到了需要的东西。四点了，法官大人，别忘了吃药。
